  childSummary:"When you order food on Swiggy or Zomato, a SUPER-SMART computer program instantly finds the best delivery person to pick up your food! It checks: which delivery person is closest to the restaurant, which direction they're heading, how busy they are, and how long the restaurant will take to cook your food. It tries to time everything so the delivery person arrives at the restaurant JUST as your food is ready — not too early (waiting around) and not too late (food getting cold). Then you watch the blue dot on the map moving toward you — the computer updates your arrival time every 30 seconds based on traffic! The whole system handles 2.5 MILLION orders every single day across 800 Indian cities!",
